Package: related
Type: Package
Title: related: an R package for analyzing pairwise relatedness data
        based on codominant molecular markers
Version: 0.8
Date: 2014-03-07
Author: Jack Pew, Jinliang Wang, Paul Muir, and Tim Frasier
Maintainer: Tim Frasier <timothy.frasier@smu.ca>
Description: Provides functions for calculating relatedness from codominant genetic data using any or all of seven estimators, and includes options for considering inbreeding and genotyping errors, and can estimate 95% confidence intervals.  Also includes simulation options for comparing the performance of different estimators on a given data set and estimating the expected resolution given a particular data set.
License: GPL (>= 2)
Depends: R (>= 2.15.0), tools, ggplot2
Packaged: 2014-03-19 13:05:43 UTC; j_pew
